  stimulus_text = 'A new study suggests that the more time people spend on social media, the less likely they are to engage in meaningful conversations with others. The research team found that individuals who check social media frequently are more likely to feel "lonely" and have trouble connecting with others in real life. Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
