  stimulus_text = 'In her 1954 memoir, *The Autobiography of Miss Jane Pittman*, the African American novelist,  Ernest Gaines, tells the story of an enslaved woman,  who lives to see the end of the Jim Crow era. Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
