  stimulus_text = 'The study found that people who had not been exposed to the new technology were more likely to avoid using it, even if it was more efficient than the old technology. However, people who had been exposed were more likely to use the new technology, even if it was less efficient than the old technology.  Why is this finding significant? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
