  stimulus_text = 'The author of this excerpt is using a type of figurative language known as a metaphor.  A metaphor is a figure of speech that makes a comparison between two unlike things without using words like "like" or "as." What is the most likely reason the author is using a metaphor in this passage? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
